like doing blind-- going down

00:52:11.140 --> 00:52:13.696
blind avenues or dead ends.

00:52:13.696 --> 00:52:15.820
I haven't learned to avoid
doing dead end research,

00:52:15.820 --> 00:52:19.790
but I've learned to do it
as quickly as possible.

00:52:19.790 --> 00:52:25.690
But the other thing is
people are-- whenever

00:52:25.690 --> 00:52:28.950
I write about one of these--
I'll write about some space

00:52:28.950 --> 00:52:32.080
thing, and someone will say, oh,
yeah, I don't know about that.

00:52:32.080 --> 00:52:33.800
I didn't-- I know
you worked at NASA.

00:52:33.800 --> 00:52:36.474
So you know about what
happens when the moon collides

00:52:36.474 --> 00:52:37.640
with something or something.

00:52:37.640 --> 00:52:40.610
And it's like my
formal education.

00:52:40.610 --> 00:52:42.354
I was working in a
robotics lab at NASA.

00:52:42.354 --> 00:52:44.270
And I've worked on some
virtual reality stuff.

00:52:44.270 --> 00:52:48.720
