00:56:52.570 --> 00:56:54.400
something I asked Vin
Diesel, because you

00:56:54.400 --> 00:56:55.840
have a lot in common with him.

00:56:59.339 --> 00:57:00.380
RANDALL MUNROE: OK, wait.

00:57:00.380 --> 00:57:02.310
Hang on.

00:57:02.310 --> 00:57:05.894
Before you ask your
question, which parts?

00:57:10.160 --> 00:57:11.650
AUDIENCE: I think
both of you have

00:57:11.650 --> 00:57:14.740
a real passion for geeky things.

00:57:14.740 --> 00:57:17.464
RANDALL MUNROE: Yeah, he was
a role playing guy, wasn't he?

00:57:17.464 --> 00:57:18.880
AUDIENCE: Yeah,
so I was wondering

00:57:18.880 --> 00:57:20.963
if you'd want to join us
for Dungeons and Dragons?

00:57:31.760 --> 00:57:34.790
RANDALL MUNROE: Sure, so here's
the qualifier-- the thing

00:57:34.790 --> 00:57:36.745
for this-- possibly.

00:57:39.470 --> 00:57:43.260
Coming back to this theme again,
the more social geeky pursuits,

00:57:43.260 --> 00:57:47.270
I didn't really get into
until I went away to college.

00:57:47.270 --> 00:57:52.610
And then eventually got a job
working with more geeky people.

00:57:52.610 --> 00:57:55.220
So when I was a kid, I knew
about Dungeons and Dragons

00:57:55.220 --> 00:57:57.590
but never actually
played it with people.

00:57:57.590 --> 00:58:02.270
So what I did is I got a bunch
of-- my closest exposure to it

00:58:02.270 --> 00:58:06.370
was the single player NetHack
and derivatives, Angband

00:58:06.370 --> 00:58:08.060
and stuff, which
I played through

00:58:08.060 --> 00:58:11.754
for several years every day.

00:58:11.754 --> 00:58:13.545
So all of my Dungeons
and Dragons knowledge

00:58:13.545 --> 00:58:14.680
is secondhand from that.

00:58:14.680 --> 00:58:18.550
The one time I did play Dungeons
and Dragons, the DM was like,

00:58:18.550 --> 00:58:19.410
OK, your character.

00:58:19.410 --> 00:58:21.870
You've at this point
picked up a weapon,

00:58:21.870 --> 00:58:24.509
which only you can pick it up.

00:58:24.509 --> 00:58:25.550
It's magically enchanted.

00:58:25.550 --> 00:58:28.940
If anyone else-- it's a
10-pound ax-- or something,

00:58:28.940 --> 00:58:33.400
and if anyone else picks it
up, it weighs 1,000 pounds.

00:58:33.400 --> 00:58:36.740
If anyone else touches it, in
fact, it weighs 1,000 pounds.

00:58:36.740 --> 00:58:40.450
And I was immediately
like, OK, wait a minute.

00:58:40.450 --> 00:58:43.440
Is there a water
wheel in this town?

00:58:43.440 --> 00:58:48.730
Can I get someone else from the
party or a peasant or someone?

00:58:48.730 --> 00:58:50.624
I want to strap the
ax to the water wheel,

00:58:50.624 --> 00:58:53.040
and have the handle sticking
out, like my hand on one side

00:58:53.040 --> 00:58:54.414
and their hand on
the other side.

00:58:54.414 --> 00:58:56.140
And we'll get it spinning.

00:58:56.140 --> 00:58:57.694
And then we'll have it weighted.

00:58:57.694 --> 00:59:00.110
So it's really heavy, but then
it comes around to my side,

00:59:00.110 --> 00:59:01.360
and I touch it, and
suddenly it's light,

00:59:01.360 --> 00:59:02.800
and the it starts spinning
faster and faster.

00:59:02.800 --> 00:59:05.070
And then we get it spinning
up to the speed that's

00:59:05.070 --> 00:59:08.710
the maximum speed that the
water wheel can handle.

00:59:08.710 --> 00:59:11.750
And then we pull the axles
out so it drops to the ground.

00:59:11.750 --> 00:59:15.510
And then we've got
this giant heavy water

00:59:15.510 --> 00:59:18.050
wheel spinning at
a fantastic rate.

00:59:18.050 --> 00:59:20.890
It'll go tearing across the
landscape toward the enemies

00:59:20.890 --> 00:59:23.485
who we're trying to fight.

00:59:32.420 --> 00:59:34.610
There was this very
nice woman in college

00:59:34.610 --> 00:59:37.460
who invited me to play that one
time and then didn't invite me

00:59:37.460 --> 00:59:39.580
back.

00:59:39.580 --> 00:59:44.310
My D&amp;D experience is limited,
but I would love to try it out.

00:59:44.310 --> 00:59:45.740
AUDIENCE: Thank you very much.

00:59:45.740 --> 00:59:47.740
RANDALL MUNROE: And thank you.

